tweet: But the sharp price declines in $Luna, compounded by large amounts of liquidations on Terra’s lending protocol Anchor, drove redemptions from $Luna to $UST to exceed $80 million, forcing $UST to trade at a discount.  /18
name: Route 2 FI 🌖👻

tweet: $UST relies on $Luna for its stability.  The Terra protocol acts as a market maker, making sure that when the supply of $UST goes up, the $Luna supply goes down, and vice versa.   The system is designed to handle $20 million of redemptions with a 2% spread.   /17
